---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Ballet — Dance Terms That Score Big"
  description="Ballet and dance words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. JETÉ (11pts), BARRE (7pts), PLIÉ (6pts). Ballet vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble ballet words, dance scrabble terms, jete scrabble points, plie scrabble, barre scrabble word, ballet vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Ballet — Dance Terms That Score Big","description":"Ballet and dance words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. JETÉ (11pts), BARRE (7pts), PLIÉ (6pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-ballet"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is JETE a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! JETE scores 11 points (J=8, E=1, T=1, E=1). It's a ballet jump where one leg is thrown forward. The J tile (8pts) provides most of the scoring power. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS without the accent mark."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is BARRE worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"BARRE scores 7 points (B=3, A=1, R=1, R=1, E=1). It's the horizontal bar dancers hold for balance exercises. The B tile (3pts) carries the scoring. BARRE also hooks to BARRED (9pts) and BARRES (8pts)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is PLIE valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PLIE scores 6 points (P=3, L=1, I=1, E=1). It's a ballet move where you bend your knees. Played without the accent in Scrabble. At 4 letters it's a perfect gap filler, and hooks to PLIED (8pts) and PLIES (7pts)."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Ballet — Dance Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Ballet terminology gives Scrabble players elegant short words with surprising scoring power. JETE delivers 11 points in just 4 letters thanks to the J tile. PLIE and BARRE are compact plays that fit tight boards perfectly. All are played without accents in Scrabble — the dictionary accepts the anglicised spellings.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JETE (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BARRE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PLIE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">POINTE</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Ballet Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">JETE — 11 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">J=8, E=1, T=1, E=1 · 4 letters · J dump</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A ballet leap where one leg is thrown forward and the other pushes off. At just 4 letters, JETE averages 2.75 points per tile — the highest efficiency of any common J word. It fits anywhere on the board and only needs two E tiles plus T.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🩰 BARRE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · B=3, A=1, R=1, R=1, E=1 · Balance bar</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💃 PLIE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">6 pts · P=3, L=1, I=1, E=1 · Knee bend</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🦶 POINTE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · P=3, O=1, I=1, N=1, T=1, E=1 · Toe dancing</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌀 PIROUETTE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · P=3, I=1, R=1, O=1, U=1, E=1, T=1, T=1, E=1 · Spin</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Ballet Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TUTU</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ADAGIO</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TENDU</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RELEVE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FONDU</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ARABESQUE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">20pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Ballet Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">JETE is the best short J word:</span> At 4 letters and 11 points, JETE has better points-per-tile than JO (9pts/2 tiles = 4.5) but is more flexible since it uses common E and T tiles. Perfect for dumping J.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PLIE hooks in multiple directions:</span> PLIE→PLIED (8pts), PLIER (7pts), PLIES (7pts). A 4-letter word with 3 common extensions gives you setup play potential on tight boards.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BARRE uses double-R:</span> Drawing two R tiles can feel wasteful. BARRE burns both in a 5-letter word while the B (3pts) adds scoring. It's also a great parallel play alongside short words.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Ballet words are <span class="text-white font-medium">short, hook-friendly, and use the J tile</span> — one of the hardest letters to play well. JETE alone justifies learning this category. Add PLIE and BARRE for two more 4-5 letter plays that fit anywhere.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-dance/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Dance</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-j-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best J Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/foreign-words-valid-in-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Foreign Words Valid in Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid ballet term instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
